{"author":{"id":"19f7b1c1979130a0a4bb24e0bdd956ab6003989829075cea146ff64dd88f08a2"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1676579582,"nonce":"M4OTlqjSLaXw+vt8Px04iO1mw54=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDODBZtRc5eq-jd","github-url":"https://github.com/dandi/dandi-cli/issues/1211","origin":"github"},"title":"[Bug]: can't run validate on a stand-alone file","message":"This and some related issues came up while I was helping a user upload their data to DANDI earlier today.\n\nI'm used to being able to run `dandi validate some_nwbfile.nwb` and have it tell me if it's valid or not. In fact, the [documentation on the archive](https://www.dandiarchive.org/handbook/13_upload/#data-uploadmanagement-workflow) still suggest this as the workflow prior to doing anything else.\n\nYet I know get an error using `dandi==0.49.0`\n\n```\ndandi validate test_upload.nwb\n[DANDI.NO_DANDISET_FOUND] test_upload.nwb — File is not inside a Dandiset\n```\n\nI feel like the `DANDI.NO_DANDISET_FOUND` check should not be run when the file is not yet inside the dandiset.\n\nEither that or someone needs to update the documentation for everything related to this.","files":null}]}